trans-unit.source: Step 9: Build and Deploy the Solution
trans-unit.target: Step 9: Build and Deploy the Solution

trans-unit.source: By now, you have finished creating the application.
trans-unit.target: By now, you have finished creating the application.

trans-unit.source: In this step, you build and deploy the application under your <token>af_integration</token> subscription.
trans-unit.target: In this step, you build and deploy the application under your <token>af_integration</token> subscription.

trans-unit.source: To build and deploy the solution
trans-unit.target: To build and deploy the solution

trans-unit.source: In Visual Studio, right click the <embeddedLabel>FlatFile_Bridge</embeddedLabel> solution, and then click <embeddedLabel>Build Solution</embeddedLabel>.
trans-unit.target: In Visual Studio, right click the <embeddedLabel>FlatFile_Bridge</embeddedLabel> solution, and then click <embeddedLabel>Build Solution</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: Once the build succeeds, right click the <embeddedLabel>FlatFile_Bridge</embeddedLabel> solution, and then click <embeddedLabel>Deploy Solution</embeddedLabel>.
trans-unit.target: Once the build succeeds, right click the <embeddedLabel>FlatFile_Bridge</embeddedLabel> solution, and then click <embeddedLabel>Deploy Solution</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: In the deployment window, the <embeddedLabel>Deployment Endpoint</embeddedLabel> is a read-only property and the value is derived from the <embeddedLabel>BizTalk Service URL/Namespace</embeddedLabel> set in the message flow surface.
trans-unit.target: In the deployment window, the <embeddedLabel>Deployment Endpoint</embeddedLabel> is a read-only property and the value is derived from the <embeddedLabel>BizTalk Service URL/Namespace</embeddedLabel> set in the message flow surface.

trans-unit.source: However, you must provide the ACS Namespace for <token>af_integration</token>, Issuer Name, and Shared Secret.
trans-unit.target: However, you must provide the ACS Namespace for <token>af_integration</token>, Issuer Name, and Shared Secret.

trans-unit.source: The Visual Studio Output pane displays the deployment progress and result.
trans-unit.target: The Visual Studio Output pane displays the deployment progress and result.

trans-unit.source: The URL where the bridge is deployed is also displayed in the Output pane.
trans-unit.target: The URL where the bridge is deployed is also displayed in the Output pane.

trans-unit.source: For this tutorial, the bridge is deployed at <codeInline>http://<legacyItalic>%%amp;lt;mybiztalkservicename%%amp;gt;</legacyItalic>.biztalk.windows.net/default/<codeFeaturedElement>ClaimsProcessing</codeFeaturedElement></codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: For this tutorial, the bridge is deployed at <codeInline>http://<legacyItalic>%%amp;lt;mybiztalkservicename%%amp;gt;</legacyItalic>.biztalk.windows.net/default/<codeFeaturedElement>ClaimsProcessing</codeFeaturedElement></codeInline>.
